The article summarizes a press briefing given by White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre and FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell. They discussed the preparations and response efforts for Hurricane Ian, which is expected to make landfall in Florida. President Biden has mobilized the full force of the federal government to support the people of Florida, and the administration is closely coordinating with state and local officials. The focus is on ensuring the safety of residents through evacuation orders and providing resources for search and rescue, power restoration, and food and water distribution. The briefing also touched on other topics, including the ongoing recovery efforts in Puerto Rico, potential waivers of the Jones Act, and the President's commitment to lowering healthcare costs for seniors.